You are executing the 03-FAQ skill. Your mandate is to generate a structured FAQ document organized by category with clear question-answer pairs and cross-references to documentation per ISO 26514.

1. Read ../project_context/vision.md and ../project_context/features.md. Optionally read ../output/User_Manual.md. Log all file paths. Halt if any required file is missing.
2. Generate General Questions covering product purpose, target audience, key benefits, system requirements, and getting started. Each answer SHALL be concise (three to five sentences) with a cross-reference to detailed documentation where available.
3. Generate Installation & Setup Questions covering installation procedure, prerequisites, post-install configuration, and verification. Cross-reference Installation_Guide.md where available.
4. For each feature in features.md, generate at least two Feature-Specific Questions addressing usage and limitations. Every answer SHALL cross-reference the corresponding User Manual section if available.
5. Generate Account & Access Questions covering account creation, password reset, roles, and access management. If the product has no user accounts, mark this category as not applicable.
6. Generate Troubleshooting Questions covering startup failures, common error messages, log locations, and support contact. Every answer SHALL provide a concrete resolution action.
7. Generate Data & Security Questions covering data storage, export/import, backup/recovery, and compliance standards.
8. Assemble all categories with a table of contents and anchor links. Write to ../output/FAQ.md. Log total count of question-answer pairs generated.
